Key Match Events: The Dodgers used a four-run fourth inning to push their lead atop the NL West to four games with a 6-3 win over the Orioles.
Colton Cowser hit a three-run homer in the fifth inning for the Orioles.
Pre-Game Insights: The Dodgers were aware of what had taken place around the league, with 29 games left in the regular season entering the day, every team in playoff contention is scoreboard watching to check in on what their opponents have done on that particular night.
The Dodgers saw the D-backs and Padres, the two teams chasing them in the National League West, had lost their respective games. It was an opportunity to gain a game on both.
Post-Match Reflections: Dave Roberts said, 'Great homestand, really good baseball. Played against teams that are in pennant races, preparing for the postseason. And I thought we showed well. I don’t think it was a litmus test or anything, but it’s still good to go out there and find ways to win baseball games. I thought we did it in different ways throughout the homestand.'
Blake Treinen said, 'I really just want to be the best in baseball at whatever my [role] is. Whatever the role in the bullpen. I just want to be the best at what I do.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers finished off the nine-game homestand with a 7-2 record.
The Dodgers will continue to evaluate their options over the next five weeks, with Bobby Miller among those options.
Others: No other significant mentions in the article.
